msgid "Security in Odoo"
msgstr ""

# bf5cf2a3468e4bfcbb7da46dd4c3a278
#: ../../reference/security.rst:9
msgid ""
"Aside from manually managing access using custom code, Odoo provides two "
"main data-driven mechanisms to manage or restrict access to data."
msgstr ""

# b9aa480cc3e14de990c7498fe41023a5
#: ../../reference/security.rst:12
msgid ""
"Both mechanisms are linked to specific users through *groups*: a user "
"belongs to any number of groups, and security mechanisms are associated "
"to groups, thus applying security mechamisms to users."
msgstr ""

# 32fe83c7bba14b67befbd6a0a4566609
#: ../../reference/security.rst:19
msgid "Access Control"
msgstr ""

# 958833421345479ba8b707f617b46497
#: ../../reference/security.rst:21
msgid ""
"Managed by the ``ir.model.access`` records, defines access to a whole "
"model."
msgstr ""

# e0671bbb2c3f4f359a05685c832ac132
#: ../../reference/security.rst:23
msgid ""
"Each access control has a model to which it grants permissions, the "
"permissions it grants and optionally a group."
msgstr ""

# 9836cf43c6bc43b7b0be49bbf3b4d5e4
#: ../../reference/security.rst:26
msgid ""
"Access controls are additive, for a given model a user has access all "
"permissions granted to any of its groups: if the user belongs to one "
"group which allows writing and another which allows deleting, they can "
"both write and delete."
msgstr ""

# 6692176f2f754b80a429dd28a5266ecb
#: ../../reference/security.rst:31
msgid ""
"If no group is specified, the access control applies to all users, "
"otherwise it only applies to the members of the given group."
msgstr ""

# b295badb486d419eae48715757fe05e3
#: ../../reference/security.rst:34
msgid ""
"Available permissions are creation (``perm_create``), searching and "
"reading (``perm_read``), updating existing records (``perm_write``) and "
"deleting existing records (``perm_unlink``)"
msgstr ""

# 8fa1d20d305d49f0a881e937d34373d8
#: ../../reference/security.rst:41
msgid "Record Rules"
msgstr ""

# 4ed1e4b7c1844ac0b27bd456894652f7
#: ../../reference/security.rst:43
msgid ""
"Record rules are conditions that records must satisfy for an operation "
"(create, read, update or delete) to be allowed. It is applied record-by-"
"record after access control has been applied."
msgstr ""

# 8df01b07c25a48af88191b34821c5756
#: ../../reference/security.rst:47
msgid "A record rule has:"
msgstr ""

# c5cf7a96076646508a14b3b638b4ecd4
#: ../../reference/security.rst:49
msgid "a model on which it applies"
msgstr ""

# c0e13e60ea0e493f9ba46bfce3df2ced
#: ../../reference/security.rst:50
msgid ""
"a set of permissions to which it applies (e.g. if ``perm_read`` is set, "
"the rule will only be checked when reading a record)"
msgstr ""

# 879d39fe92b1425cb1a43a583f002d13
#: ../../reference/security.rst:52
msgid ""
"a set of user groups to which the rule applies, if no group is specified "
"the rule is *global*"
msgstr ""

# 266e27f515424da89ec1b0f849a61f13
#: ../../reference/security.rst:54
msgid ""
"a :ref:`domain <reference/orm/domains>` used to check whether a given "
"record matches the rule (and is accessible) or does not (and is not "
"accessible). The domain is evaluated with two variables in context: "
"``user`` is the current user's record and ``time`` is the `time module`_"
msgstr ""

# 35f48ba3714b447aaa38294daede2c1c
#: ../../reference/security.rst:59
msgid ""
"Global rules and group rules (rules restricted to specific groups versus "
"groups applying to all users) are used quite differently:"
msgstr ""

# 9ee3f3f493f9432684667f78d7d8469c
#: ../../reference/security.rst:62
msgid ""
"Global rules are subtractive, they *must all* be matched for a record to "
"be accessible"
msgstr ""

# 19e19e9ba5b1458ea38ba9ef3e761628
#: ../../reference/security.rst:64
msgid ""
"Group rules are additive, if *any* of them matches (and all global rules "
"match) then the record is accessible"
msgstr ""

# 74dd3a9b8dc0410b9c3eb9cb5a3e3494
#: ../../reference/security.rst:67
msgid ""
"This means the first *group rule* restricts access, but any further "
"*group rule* expands it, while *global rules* can only ever restrict "
"access (or have no effect)."
msgstr ""

# 1d3d4d238b74431798803b785b2139b9
#: ../../reference/security.rst:71
msgid "record rules do not apply to the Administrator user"
msgstr ""

# 77d16471a478417aaa5ba4c5d6d22dc4
#: ../../reference/security.rst:74
msgid "although access rules do"
msgstr ""

